nternational_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999884003047, \"rank\": 1.1599717120824972e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999997268358047, \"rank\": 1.5675888506666892e-07, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/CFP\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2034 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"a vote\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"its second Games\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 1,000 sports fans gathered in downtown Salt Lake City at 3 a.m. local time \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 11 a.m. in Paris \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 to watch the long-anticipated announcement on a livestream.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9703107687281359, \"rank\": 0.030597641148849462, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999884003047, \"rank\": 1.1599717120824972e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"About 1,000 sports fans\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"3 a.m.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"11 a.m.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"the long-anticipated announcement\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"a livestream\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some dressed in ski gear despite the summer heat, while others donned Team USA merchandise and waved flags bearing images of the Olympic Rings.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999839205510308, \"rank\": 1.4955516161731561e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.989276651283857e-35, \"text\": \"Olympic Rings\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ski gear\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer heat\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd erupted in cheers as Olympic officials made their final decision to return to a city where they said the local enthusiasm was palpable, even two decades after it first hosted the Games.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The crowd\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"cheers\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"their final decision\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"the local enthusiasm\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Utah's state capital was the only candidate for 2034 after the IOC gave Salt Lake City exclusive negotiating rights last year.\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1179, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999997268358047, \"rank\": 1.5675888506666892e-07, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1242, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.20199050619662e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9703107687281359, \"rank\": 0.030597641148849462, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only candidate\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate change and high operational costs have reduced the number of cities willing and able to stage the Winter Games.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Climate change\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"high operational costs\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Games\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Utah quickly capitalized on the low interest elsewhere, pitching itself to Olympic officials as an eager repeat host if the IOC eventually adopts a permanent rotation of cities for winter editions of the world's biggest multi-sport showcase.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999997268358047, \"rank\": 1.5675888506666892e-07, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.20199050619662e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the low interest\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"an eager repeat host\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1543}, {\"ngram\": \"a permanent rotation\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"winter editions\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest multi-sport showcase\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic Games Executive Director Christophe Dubi said Salt Lake City would be a prime candidate for such a plan.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1713, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dub\\u00ed\", \"score\": 0.9122799604624169, \"rank\": 0.09615453479896953, \"text\": \"Dubi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dub\\u00ed\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dub\\u00ed\"}, {\"begin\": 1723, \"end\": 1737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9703107687281359, \"rank\": 0.030597641148849462, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a prime candidate\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"such a plan\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1780}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local leaders had their sights set on hosting multiple times even before Salt Lake City welcomed its first Games, bid team spokesperson Tom Kelly said.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1856, \"end\": 1870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9703107687281359, \"rank\": 0.030597641148849462, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kelly_(musician)\", \"score\": 0.799125854196736, \"rank\": 0.24283458829246402, \"text\": \"Tom Kelly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kelly_(musician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kelly_(musician)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Local leaders\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"their sights\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple times\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"its first Games\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remnants of the 2002 Games are visible throughout the city and have kept the Olympic fever alive.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Remnants\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2002 Games\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1993}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic fever\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organizers of the 2034 Games touted that enduring enthusiasm throughout the selection process and showed visiting Olympic officials how they have preserved nearly all of the venues used in 2002.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The organizers\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2034 Games\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"that enduring enthusiasm\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2098}, {\"ngram\": \"the selection process\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly all\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"the venues\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Enthusiasm for the Games was always our feeling, on the first minute to the last minute, in every interaction we had, both at the venues and in our meetings with athletes, sports leaders, politicians and the private sector,\\\" Karl Stoss, chairman of the International Olympic Committee's Future Host Commission, told the full committee Wednesday morning in Paris.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2488, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999884003047, \"rank\": 1.1599717120824972e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"w